    <!-- Changelog 0.1.8 -->
    <string name="changelog_version_0_1_8">v0.1.8</string>
    <string name="changelog_content_0_1_8">- Fixed `_chk` suffix not being recognized as Traditional Chinese.\n- Fixed language file parsing crash in certain cases.\n- Added Accompanist Flow Layout dependency.\n- Optimized translator page filter UI.\n- Changed keyword highlighting color to yellow.</string>

    <!-- Changelog 0.1.9 -->
    <string name="changelog_version_0_1_9">v0.1.9</string>
    <!-- Changelog 0.2.2 -->
    <string name="changelog_version_0_2_2">v0.2.2</string>
    <string name="changelog_content_0_2_2">- Calibration library comparison and merge: see diffs before importing, selectively merge entries.\n- Key prefix grouping: translation entries grouped by prefix (e.g. actor.*, windows.*) with collapsible headers.\n- \"No Translation Needed\" button: mark entries that should keep source text, excluded from untranslated count.\n- Create language fix: support underscore format (zh_CN), fix edge cases.\n- Fix search navigation offset in grouped view; auto-expand collapsed groups to reveal search results.</string>
    <!-- Changelog 0.2.0 -->
    <string name="changelog_version_0_2_0">v0.2.0</string>
    <string name="changelog_content_0_2_0">[New Features]\n- Translation engines: 10 engines supported (5 free web engines + 5 official API engines).\n- New Baidu Web Translate engine (BaiduWebEngine): uses fanyi.baidu.com web API with full token/gtk signing, no API key needed.\n- DeepLX zero-config: built-in public endpoints (api.deeplx.org), works without any user configuration.\n- Engine reordering: 5 free web engines listed first, start translating immediately without setup.\n- Global dictionary: cross-group translation lookup — searches current group → legacy format → all groups globally (most recent timestamp wins).\n- Translation progress bar: LinearProgressIndicator + percentage (2 decimal places, e.g. 56.78%), always visible.\n- Search and Replace buttons: new Find and Replace All buttons, supports case-sensitive and exact match modes.\n- Dungeon-themed search buttons: scroll/wand pixel icons + dungeon accent colors in PD theme.\n- One-click translate per entry via current engine, results shown as chips.\n- Per-group base language override for engine source language.\n- DELETED view supports undo: staged deletions shown as grey cards with undo button.\n\n[Pixel Dungeon Theme]\n- Default theme changed to Pixel Dungeon — dungeon experience from first launch.\n- 24-hour color system: expanded from 6 time zones to 24 hourly zones, each with unique dungeon scene colors.\n- All colors sourced from real MLPD game data (Window.java / CharSprite.java / FistSprite / Level sources).\n- Scenes include: Sewers, Goo, Garden, Prison, Tengu, Caves, Crystal Caves, Dwarf City, Dwarf King, Demon Halls, Evil Eyes, Scorpio Nest, Yog-Dzewa, all Fists, Last Level.\n- Enhanced brick wall textures: moss, blood stains, crystal deposits based on zone color2.\n- 24 unique flame color palettes (hellfire red, toxic green, lantern yellow, crystal blue, arcane purple, etc.).\n- Bottom magic pool glow varies by chapter (lava, sewer water, candlelight, crystal reflection, MLPD cyan magic, blood pool).\n- Navigation icons: 6 icon sets covering all 24 hours.\n- Real pixel fonts (fusion_pixel.ttf + pixel_font.ttf).\n- 13 pixel vector icons (16×16 viewport, pixel-perfect).\n- Easter egg: dungeon zone name and depth shown in settings.\n\n[Improvements]\n- Dictionary keys include group name dimension — multi-group dictionaries no longer conflict.\n- Snackbar events work globally across all screens.\n- UI polish: ElevatedCard sections, unified icon headers, scrollable engine config dialog.\n- Search/Replace button layout: checkboxes and buttons on separate rows, buttons equal-width.\n- Import button uses FilledTonalButton, export button in dedicated card.\n\n[Bug Fixes]\n- Fixed legacy language code recognition: _in (Indonesian), _iw (Hebrew), _ji (Yiddish) etc. now correctly join language groups.\n- Export failure protection: ZIP write errors no longer silently clear staged changes.\n- Language code validation and auto-normalization, invalid codes (e.g. xxx) are blocked.\n- Draft validation includes source text SHA-256 digest for stricter mismatch detection.\n- No-op staged changes no longer enable save button or trigger auto-save.\n- Fixed LinearProgressIndicator parameter type error.\n- Fixed normalizedCode variable name conflict causing compilation error.\n\n[Workspace &amp; Dictionary]\n- Scoped workspace: staged edits are preserved per language group — switching groups no longer loses unsaved translations.\n- Aggregate \"all\" group: select all groups at once for dictionary save/apply operations.\n- Editable dictionary preview: edit source text and translation directly in the preview dialog.\n- Multi-scope auto-save: crash recovery now preserves staged edits across all groups, not just the active one.\n- Copy button added to all translation card types (normal, diff, deleted, staged-deleted, preview).\n- New language creation: input clears only on success, not on validation failure.\n- Translation cards and badges now use theme shapes instead of hardcoded rounded corners — Pixel Dungeon cut-corner style applied consistently.</string>

    <string name="changelog_content_0_1_9">- Added batch import for multiple .properties files.\n- Added auto-save draft system with SHA-256 validation.\n- Added Translation Memory (TM) with fuzzy matching suggestions.\n- Improved language selector: displays localized names via Locale API.\n- Supports mixed filename formats (underscore/hyphen/script tags).\n- Filter buttons upgraded to Material 3 FilterChip.\n- Pagination controls compacted with icon buttons.\n- Added empty state guidance for translator screen.\n- All hardcoded strings moved to resources for full i18n support.\n- Export now shows success Snackbar feedback.</string>
